in dps (by the means of FT items).<br>
<br>
FT items that should stack, and be much much more common.<br>
(At least as RBB/RBG/CoF and other items are for melees).<br>
<br>
Make FT0.5 items, i dont care. <br>
<br>
I believe some classes are perfect for killing a certain type<br>
of mobs and that many of us (including myself) often complain<br>
but tend to forget the mob variety factor.<br>
<br>
Out of these 11 mobs, who will do the most dmg on a &quot;standart&quot; fight ?<br>
<br>
Seb shaman frog (slow) :<br>
Seb knight frog  :<br>
Gorenaire (AoE slow) :<br>
Talendor :<br>
Ikatar :<br>
Aaryonar (Atk debuff) :<br>
Zlexak  (AoE slow)<br>
Dagarn :<br>
Vulak (AoE slow) :<br>
King Tormax :<br>
Ssra Serpents (high ac) :<br>
<br>
Melees out damage casters on simple mobs, but put a<br>
AoE : Slow / Atk Debuff / DD / DoT on that mob<br>
and you will see melee dmg go down.<br>
<br>
I can come out and nuke between AoEs, melees cant.<br>
<br>
Whats better :<br>
G1 -Having 2war 1rogue 2monk + 1 CLERIC<br>
G2 -Having 5wiz + 1 druid/shaman<br>
<br>
I think G2, will do the same dmg and NOT DRAIN a cleric from<br>
the rotation <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvarkis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varkis</A> at: 3/10/02 11:18:08 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 464<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/02 1:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Melee vs Wizards = Depends on mob types</span><hr size=1> You forgot to mention how a good number of mobs require the casters to be in melee range, resist all spells(Spite golems are 99 percent resistant to fire, cold, and magic LURES), and how the mana bar for casters would limit our damage output, even if our spells wern't resisted.   <br>
<br>
Now, if you want to compare damage output in zones such as Acrylia Caverns, where melee damage output is limited by the high AC of the mobs, then yes,there's SOME balance being done, but this sort of change needs to be done across the board to balance the classes, not in only one or two zones.<br>
<br>
If we can cast 10 Elnerick's Electrical Rending on a single bar of mana, that's decent, but it doesn't compare to melees with Primal weapons, and other high end melee weapons.<br>
<br>
Your balance also doesn't take into account how twinked melees can do MUCH MUCH MUCH higher levels of damage pre-60 than any caster could hope for due to twinking and the lack of spells available.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 60 Wizard<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 1500<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/11/02 9:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Melee vs Wizards = Depends on mob types</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> the mana bar for casters would limit our damage output, even if our spells wern't resisted<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Since you brought that up, I'd just like you to know that melees have a bar that limits their attacking too. It's just not working like our mana bar does.<br>
I'm sure all of you know that melee combat reduces their stamina pool, and once it goes down to 0, they are supposed to be fatigued. Well, that only happens until they hit 100 base stamina, and then they have no side effects of running out of stamina.<br>
See, I always though that that was the difference between casters and melee classes. We use our mana pools, and they use their stamina pools. Except it doesn't work out like that, which puts us in our current state.<br>
Melee classes, once they have 100 stamina, only rely on their HP to do damage. As long as they're alive, they're doing damage. Casters can't do that, and never have been able to. Casters melee skills are far to low, and most would say if you're not medding when OOM, then you're a retard.<br>
<br>
If Stamina were based on the same tables as mana is, then we'd be closer to being balanced with melee classes. You'd see melee classes getting tired during combat, and we'd take over with our damage. When a melee class got enough stamina to swing their weapon, they could. That would take care of their unbalanced way of being able to continuously output damage as long as they're alive.<br>
All those instant stamina pool spells like invigor would have to go though, and be replaced with spells that regen stamina like clarity/breeze regen mana.<br>
Tanks would start having downtime that should be about the same as ours. That would change the way melees look at casters; Being nothing but a slow down to a normal exp grind group.  <p><center>
